Definition of non-deterministic finite automata (NFA)
In deterministic automata the next state is predictable but in non-deterministic (NFA) there could be random and multiple different next states.
epsilon means emptry string/input and could start an empty state

NFA will show a 0 in the diagram meaning what is accepted

L = { Set of all string that end with 0 }

NFA allows states to loopback

tuples = Q, sigma, q not q(o), f, del

Q = set of all state {A,B}
sigma (E) = inputs - {0,1}
Qo = start state {A}
F = Set of final states {B}
S(del) = QxSigma->__
Ax0->A times 0 goes to A
Ax0->B also goes to B
Ax1->A
Bx0->FI
BX1->FI

Inputs can be calculated into one or multiple results

A->A,B,C,AB,AC,BC,ABC,FI... permutations are not allowed in list

to calculate FI get the number of states and number of possibilities subtract them and raise by 2. result for previous examples is 2^Q(2 elevated by the states)

