🧩 Exercise 1 — DFA (Deterministic)
📌 Problem

Given a Deterministic Finite Automaton:

States: {q0, q1}
Alphabet: {a, b}
Start: q0
Accepting: {q1}

Transitions:

δ(q0, a) = q1
δ(q0, b) = q0
δ(q1, a) = q1
δ(q1, b) = q0

👉 Question:
Does the DFA accept the string "abba"?

✅ Answer (step-by-step)

Start at q0

Input	State
a	q0 → q1
b	q1 → q0
b	q0 → q0
a	q0 → q1

Final state = q1 ✅ (accepting)

👉 Result: ACCEPTED

