🧩 Exercise 1 — NFA (Nondeterministic)
📌 Problem

Given a Nondeterministic Finite Automaton:

States: {q0, q1}
Alphabet: {a, b}
Start: q0
Accepting: {q1}

🔄 Transitions

δ(q0, a) = {q0, q1}
δ(q0, b) = {q0}
δ(q1, a) = ∅
δ(q1, b) = ∅

👉 Question:

Does the NFA accept the string "a"?

✅ Answer (step-by-step)

Start at {q0}

Input	State
a	{q0} → {q0, q1}

Final states = {q0, q1}
Accepting state = q1 ✅

👉 Result: ACCEPTED

